  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (software-fault gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver pipeline is software-intensive, coupling an OpenFOAM-based rotating-reference-frame solver with a Python post-processing layer that computes the relative hemolysis index (RH). All validation runs completed nominally; no solver-fault injection or numerical-instability stress testing was performed beyond a single documented convergence check at the nominal operating point.",
