      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver release with documented build verification; unit tests passing for all compiled modules.",
      "rationale": "OpenFOAM v9 release tag used; build verification log archived. Python hemolysis post-processor under Git version control with tagged release. Unit tests cover steady-state solver modules. Runtime fault injection (e.g., deliberate NaN injection, thread-safety probing of the MPI parallel decomposition) was not included in the SQA test suite; the assessment team considered nominal unit-test passage sufficient for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy test on canonical rotating-cavity benchmark achieves theoretical second-order convergence.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation on a rotating-cavity benchmark confirms second-order spatial convergence (observed order 1.94). Temporal discretisation verified on a transient impeller-passage case. No edge-case inputs (zero flow, near-zero viscosity, degenerate cell geometries) were exercised during code verification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% for RH at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study (1.2 M, 3.6 M, 10.8 M cells) performed at the 3500 RPM / 5 L/min reference point. GCI = 2.1%. Single-point GCI applied to remaining operating points by similarity argument. Mesh-refinement runs at 1.2 M cells produced one convergence failure (noted in VR-04); this event was classified as a mesh-quality artefact rather than a software fault and no further investigation was conducted."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions reproduced in CFD to within ±2% for flow rate and ±1% for rotational speed.",
      "rationale": "FDA experimental data from the generic centrifugal pump inter-laboratory study used as validation reference. CFD boundary conditions matched to reported experimental values: flow rate ±1.3%, rotational speed ±0.6%. Blood viscosity set to 0.0035 Pa·s (Newtonian approximation) consistent with experimental protocol."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalised prediction error for RH < 15% at all five validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Normalised errors for all five validation runs range from 2.0% to 9.0%, all within the 15% acceptance threshold. Comparison methodology follows ASME V&V 20-2009 standard for experimental uncertainty quantification. All solver outputs were produced by nominally completing runs with no flagged exceptions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (RH) directly maps to clinical hemolysis metric; secondary QoIs (wall shear stress, exposure time) support mechanistic understanding.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index RH is the regulatory-accepted scalar metric for pump-induced hemolysis per FDA guidance. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) integrates shear stress and exposure time along Lagrangian particle tracks, both of which are computed by the CFD solver and directly relevant to the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
